(at early and late times) is bounded (e.g, Deltaalphamax < 0.4 for a = 10); Deltaalphamax slowly increases with a, converging to Deltaalphamax ~ 1 at very large a values. Therefore, no optical rebrightening is expected in this case as well. In the X-rays, while the asymptotic flux is unaffected by the density jump, the fluctuations in alpha are found to be comparable to those in the optical. Finally, we discuss the implications of our results for the origin of the observed fluctuations in several GRB afterglows.},
